# Motion & Transitions — Animation with Purpose

> Animation without purpose is decoration. Animation with purpose is communication.
> Every millisecond must have a reason.

---

## FUNDAMENTAL MOTION PRINCIPLES

### 1. Functional, Not Decorative
- Animation must COMMUNICATE something: relationship, hierarchy, state, or direction
- If you remove the animation and nothing changes in comprehension → the animation is unnecessary

### 2. Fast and Smooth
- Perception of speed > actual speed
- Animations should START fast and decelerate (ease-out)
- The user should not WAIT for the animation

### 3. Natural and Physical
- Objects don't teleport — they MOVE
- Objects don't stop abruptly — they DECELERATE
- Heavy objects move slower than light objects

### 4. Consistent
- Same type of transition for the same type of action
- Same duration for the same category of animation
- Consistent easing curves throughout the app

