## EASING CURVES (Acceleration Curves)

### Easing Types:

| Curve | CSS | Use | Feel |
|---|---|---|---|
| **ease-out** | cubic-bezier(0, 0, 0.2, 1) | Elements ENTERING | Fast start, smooth end |
| **ease-in** | cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 1, 1) | Elements EXITING | Smooth start, fast end |
| **ease-in-out** | cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1) | Elements CHANGING state | Smooth-fast-smooth |
| **gentle** | Figma built-in | Elegant transitions | Very smooth, premium feel |
| **linear** | linear | Progress bars, spinners | Constant speed (robotic) |
| **spring** | Custom | Bouncy, playful UI | Overshoot and settling |

### IN FIGMA:
```javascript
// For prototyping:
easing: { type: 'EASE_IN_AND_OUT' }     // Universal default
easing: { type: 'GENTLE' }               // Premium, elegant
easing: { type: 'EASE_OUT' }             // Elements entering
easing: { type: 'EASE_IN' }              // Elements exiting
easing: { type: 'LINEAR' }               // Progress, spinners
easing: { type: 'CUSTOM_SPRING', stiffness: 300, damping: 25 }  // Spring
```

### WHEN TO USE EACH CURVE:
| Action | Curve |
|---|---|
| Screen appearing | ease-out (arrives fast, settles smooth) |
| Screen exiting | ease-in (accelerates out) |
| Modal opening | ease-out or gentle |
| Modal closing | ease-in |
| Toggle/Switch | ease-in-out |
| Fade in | ease-out |
| Fade out | ease-in |
| Value transition (counter) | ease-in-out |
| Spinner rotation | linear |

