## SMART ANIMATE IN FIGMA

### When to use:
- Elements that change size, position, color, or opacity between frames
- Micro-interactions within the same screen (expand card, move item)
- Complex transitions with multiple changing elements

### Requirements:
- **Same names**: Layers with the SAME name in both frames are animated
- **Properties that animate**: x, y, width, height, rotation, opacity, fills
- **Properties that DON'T animate**: text content, effects (needs workaround)

### TIP:
> To create a micro-interaction with SMART_ANIMATE:
> 1. Duplicate the frame (state A)
> 2. Modify the desired elements in the duplicate (state B)
> 3. Connect A → B with SMART_ANIMATE + ON_CLICK or ON_HOVER

